<subsection xml:id="subsec-squares-of-numbers-from-a-calculator">
    <title>Squares of numbers from a calculator</title>
    <p>
    A calculator is a portable device used to perform different mathematical calculations, such as addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division.    
    </p>
    <image source="/cal.jpg" width="50%">
        <shortdescription>sample of a calculator</shortdescription>
    </image>
    <p>
        <m>\textbf{How to use a calculator}</m>
    </p>
    <p>
        To start the calculator press the <m>{\color{green}\text{on}}</m> button.
    </p>
    <p>
         Given a number to work out its square, for example given <m>3</m>:
    </p>
    <p>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Press the key <kbd>3</kbd>.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Press the key <kbd>x²</kbd>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Press the key <kbd>=</kbd>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Read the number on the screen of the calculator.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </p>
    <p>
        To find the square of a decimal number e.g 4.7:
    </p>
    <p>
        Press the keys <kbd>4</kbd> then <kbd>.</kbd> finally press <kbd>7</kbd>.
    </p>
    <p>
        Press the key <kbd>x²</kbd> which means square.
    </p>
    <p>
         Press the key <kbd>=</kbd>
    </p>
    <p>
        Then read the number on the screen of the calculator.
    </p>
    <activity>
        <statement>
            <p>
               Use a calculator to work out the squares of the following numbers: 
            </p>
            <p>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>18</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>179</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>1258</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>2.9</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                           <m> 0.5987</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                           <m> 0.028</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
            <p>
                Read the number on the screen of the calculator after squaring each number.
            </p>
            <p>
                Discuss with other learners how you determine squares of numbers using a calculator.
            </p>
        </statement>
    </activity>
    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Use a calculator to work out the area of the flower garden which measures <m>0.256</m> m by <m>0.256</m> m.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                To calculate the area of the flower garden, multiply the two given dimensions:
            </p>
            <p>
               Area = <m>0.256 \times 0.256</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                Using a calculator:
            </p>
            <p>
                <ol marker="(a)">
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Press the key <kbd>0</kbd>,<kbd>.</kbd>,<kbd>2</kbd>,<kbd>5</kbd>,<kbd>6</kbd>.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Press the key <kbd>x</kbd>.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Press the key <kbd>0</kbd>,<kbd>.</kbd>,<kbd>2</kbd>,<kbd>5</kbd>,<kbd>6</kbd>.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Press the key <kbd>=</kbd>.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
            <p>
                Read the number on the screen of the calculator.
            </p>
            <p>
                Therefore, the area of the flower garden is <m>0.065536 \text{m^2}</m>.
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
</subsection>